<DocsLayout title="For Administrators" section="Notifications">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Set up email notifications to keep administrators informed about key actions and
    changes related to work orders, estimates, and service requests.
  </p>
  <p>
    You're not always in front of Field Promax — email notifications keep you updated
    on important changes even when you're away from your desk.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Work Orders:</strong> Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Work Order Settings</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Estimates:</strong> Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Estimate Settings</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Service Requests:</strong> Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Company</strong> → <strong>Service Request Settings</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Available Notifications</h2>

  <h3>Work Order Notifications</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Work Order Completion:</strong> When a schedule (visit) is marked complete by a technician</li>
    <li><strong>Work Order Closure:</strong> When a work order has been closed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Estimate Notifications</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Estimate Approval:</strong> When an estimate is approved by a customer</li>
    <li><strong>Change Request:</strong> When a change request is submitted for an estimate</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Service Request Notifications</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>New Submission:</strong> When a service request is submitted by a customer</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Other Notifications</h3>
  <p>
    Many other email notifications are available throughout Field Promax.
    Explore the settings in each module to customize what you receive.
  </p>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>
    Email notifications for administrators are configured in their respective modules:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Work Order Settings</strong> for work order notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Estimate Settings</strong> for estimate notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Service Request Settings</strong> for service request notifications</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Only administrators can configure notification settings</li>
    <li>Notifications are sent to the email addresses associated with administrator accounts</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Email notifications keep you informed</strong> even when you're away from your desk.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Enable key notifications</strong> like estimate approvals and service requests to respond quickly.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Review notification settings</strong> periodically to ensure you're receiving what you need.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
